Sure, here's a table ranking the shared philosophies of design leaders by how frequently they are mentioned:

| Shared Philosophy | Rank |
| --- | --- |
| Empathy and Understanding People's Needs | 1 |
| Simplicity and Clarity | 2 |
| Purpose and Meaning | 3 |
| Innovation and Problem-Solving | 4 |
| Creativity and Experimentation | 5 |
| Collaboration and Communication | 6 |
| Positive and Supportive Work Culture | 7 |
| Continuous Learning and Improvement | 8 |
| Taking Risks | 9 |
| Diversity and Inclusion | 10 |

Note that this ranking is based on my subjective interpretation of the quotes and philosophies shared by design leaders and may not accurately reflect their relative importance or frequency of mention in their work.
